# Session 5 — Client-Side Prediction: Bug Fixes & Bomb Passthrough

Date: 2026-04-03

---

## What Was Done

Two bugs in the client-side prediction system were diagnosed and fixed, making
local player movement smooth and collision behaviour consistent with the server.

---

## Bug 1 — Math.floor vs Math.round Collision Mismatch

### Symptom

Movement only appeared after ~4–5 seconds of holding a direction key, then the
player snapped one tile forward. Pressing a direction key showed no immediate
response.

### Root Cause

The `collides()` function in `prediction.ts` used `Math.floor` to convert a
corner's float coordinate into a tile index:

```ts
const col = Math.floor(cx);
const row = Math.floor(cy);
```

The server's `collidesWithGrid` uses `Math.round`:

```ts
const tx = Math.round(cornerX);
const ty = Math.round(cornerY);
```

At spawn tile `(1, 1)` with `HALF = 0.45`, the top-left hitbox corner sits at
`(0.55, 0.55)`:

| Method | Result | Tile | Tile type |
|--------|--------|------|-----------|
| `Math.floor(0.55)` | `0` | `(0, 0)` | `WALL_HARD` → collision! |
| `Math.round(0.55)` | `1` | `(1, 1)` | `EMPTY` → passable |

The predictor immediately detected a false collision at spawn and blocked all
movement. The server moved the player normally (using `Math.round`). Once the
accumulated server–client position error exceeded 1.5 tiles the `reconcile()`
threshold triggered a hard snap, producing the visible one-tile jump.

### Fix

Changed `collides()` to use `Math.round` on both axes, matching the server exactly.

```ts
// Before
const col = Math.floor(cx);
const row = Math.floor(cy);

// After
const col = Math.round(cx);
const row = Math.round(cy);
```

