## Bug 2 — Own-Bomb Not Passable on Client

### Symptom

After placing a bomb, the local player was immediately blocked by it and could
not walk away. The server allowed the player to walk off their own bomb normally.

### Root Cause

The server maintains a `passableBombs: Set<string>` per player. When a bomb is
placed, its ID is added to the set. Collision checks skip BOMB tiles whose index
is in the passable set. The tile is only promoted to solid once the player's
hitbox fully leaves it (checked by `hitboxOverlapsTile`).

The client predictor had no equivalent — it treated every `TileType.BOMB` tile
as unconditionally solid:

```ts
function isSolid(tile: TileType): boolean {
  return tile === TileType.WALL_HARD || tile === TileType.WALL_SOFT || tile === TileType.BOMB;
}
```

### Fix

**`prediction.ts`** — Added passable-bomb tracking mirroring the server:

1. Added `passableBombs: Map<tileIndex, {x, y}>` to `LocalPlayerPredictor`.
2. Added `addPassableBomb(tileX, tileY)` public method — called when the server
   confirms a new bomb owned by the local player.
3. `collides()` now accepts a `passable: Set<number>` parameter. BOMB tiles
   whose flat index is in `passable` are treated as walkable.
4. `hitboxOverlapsTile(px, py, tx, ty)` added — mirror of server method. Checks
   whether any of the four hitbox corners rounds to tile `(tx, ty)`.
5. In `advance()`: before moving each frame, iterate `passableBombs` and remove
   any entry whose tile the hitbox no longer overlaps. Then build the passable
   `Set` and pass it to all `collides()` calls.

```ts
// Promote passable bombs to solid once hitbox fully leaves tile
for (const [idx, pos] of this.passableBombs) {
  if (!hitboxOverlapsTile(this.px, this.py, pos.x, pos.y)) {
    this.passableBombs.delete(idx);
  }
}
const passable = new Set(this.passableBombs.keys());
```

**`main.ts`** — Registered new bombs in the `game:tick` handler, **before**
`applyDiff`, so the passable entry exists before the BOMB grid tile is written
into the client grid (preventing a single-frame block):

```ts
socket.on('game:tick', (diff) => {
  if (diff.bombs) {
    for (const bomb of Object.values(diff.bombs)) {
      if (bomb.ownerId === myPlayerId) {
        predictor.addPassableBomb(bomb.position.x, bomb.position.y);
      }
    }
  }
  gameState.applyDiff(diff);
  // ...
});
```

`passableBombs` is cleared in both `init()` and `reset()` to avoid stale state
across game rounds.

