## Invariants After This Session

- Client collision is byte-for-byte equivalent to server for walls and own-bomb passthrough.
- The only remaining client–server divergence is other players' bombs (client
  always treats them as solid, which is correct — only the bomb owner gets
  passthrough on the server too).
- `reconcile()` threshold remains at 1.5 tiles; normal prediction lead (~0.3 tiles
  at 100 ms RTT) never triggers it.
